# commitly-cli ğŸš€ğŸ¤–

> _Never write "final commit" or "modifs 2" again in your Git history._

**commitly-cli** is a stylish command-line interface powered by `Rich`, built on top of the [commitly](https://github.com/Tostenn/commitly) library. It generates smart, structured, and elegant Git commit messages for you â€” so you can focus on your code.

---

## ğŸ§  Why commitly-cli?

You run `git commit -m ""`, thenâ€¦ you freeze.

ğŸ˜© Youâ€™re thinking: â€œWhat should I write here?â€

With **commitly-cli**, let the AI do it for you.  
It reads your staged changes (`git diff --cached`), understands what youâ€™ve done, and crafts a clean, contextual message.

> Think of it as your Git copilot âœˆï¸

