## ğŸ’¥ Fun Fact: commitly-cli wrote itself

This very project is the best demo of commitly-cli.

ğŸ› ï¸ The first 2 commits were hand-written.

From the **third commit** onward, commitly-cli took the wheel.
At first, it wasn't great. Here's the actual result from its first attempt:

````bash
git commit -m "```"
````

Yes â€” triple backticks as the commit message.
Why? Because the training example used `"commit message here"`â€¦ and the AI took that **literally** ğŸ˜…

Since then, it's grown a lot â€” smarter, more structured, and reliable.

Want to see the evolution?

> Check out the Git history:
> [`git log`](https://github.com/Tostenn/commitly-cli/commits/main)

Itâ€™s like watching an AI grow from ğŸ£ to ğŸ§™â€â™‚ï¸

